column34:
Interesting viewpoints- although it still seems like a lot of surveys on political differences try to force respondents into responding one way to the very left or right. Its hard to answer somethings without wondering if the results skew into trying to shoehorn respondents as either Democrat or Republican. For example, I feel that I am conservative fiscally but very moderate or even liberal on some social policies - such that I do not feel I can be described by either party. 

I think the majority of the population tends to be a combination of both sides, and that the continued shoehorning of "left and right" is what causes a majority of problems and conflict in this country today.
